keys.name: CFG-BDS-USE_GEO_PRN
keys.description: Use BeiDou geostationary satellites (PRN 1-5 and 59-63)

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_VOLTCTRL
keys.description: Active antenna voltage control flag

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_SHORTDET
keys.description: Short antenna detection flag. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_SHORTDET_POL
keys.description: Short antenna detection polarity. Set to true if polarity of the antenna short detection is active low. Used by EXT engine.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_OPENDET
keys.description: Open antenna detection flag. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_OPENDET_POL
keys.description: Open antenna detection polarity. Set to true if polarity of the antenna open detection is active low. Used by EXT engine.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_PWRDOWN
keys.description: Power down antenna flag. Enable power down antenna logic in the event of antenna short circuit. CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_SHORTDET must be enabled to use this feature. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_PWRDOWN_POL
keys.description: Power down antenna logic polarity. Set to true if polarity of the antenna power down logic is active high. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_CFG_RECOVER
keys.description: Automatic recovery from short state flag. Enable automatic recovery from short state. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_SUP_SWITCH_PIN
keys.description: Antenna switch PIO number. Used by EXT and MADC engines.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_SUP_SHORT_PIN
keys.description: Antenna short detection PIO number. Used by EXT engine.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_SUP_OPEN_PIN
keys.description: Antenna open detection PIO number. Used by EXT engine.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_ON_SHORT_US
keys.description: Delay in microseconds between turning the antenna power supply on and enabling the antenna short circuit detection.

keys.name: CFG-HW-SENS_WOM_MODE
keys.description: Select Wake-On-Motion mode

HOST.description: Enable Wake-On-Motion feature on the host CPU.

RECEIVER.description: Enable Wake-On-Motion feature on the receiver.

BOTH.description: Enable Wake-On-Motion feature on both host CPU and receiver.

keys.name: CFG-HW-SENS_WOM_THLD
keys.description: Required acceleration on single accelerometer axis for triggering wake up, from 0 to 1 g, where g = 9.81 m/s^2. Value range is [1-255], with 1 step = 1/255 * g. For example, for 0.5 g threshold the configured value should be 128.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_SUP_ENGINE
keys.description: Select the engine used to evaluate antenna state. The EXT engine uses an external comparator for current measurement. The MADC engine uses a built-in measurement ADC and requires only a shunt resistor for current measurement. The MADC engine is supported only in selected u-blox generation 9 receivers.

EXT.description: Use the EXT engine (not available in all products)

MADC.description: Use the MADC engine (not available in all products)

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_SUP_SHORT_THR
keys.description: Threshold above which antenna short is detected. Used by MADC engine.

keys.name: CFG-HW-ANT_SUP_OPEN_THR
keys.description: Threshold below which antenna open/disconnected is detected. Used by MADC engine.

keys.description:

Only used if CFG-TP-PULSE_LENGTH_DEF=LENGTH is set.

keys.name: CFG-TP-LEN_LOCK_TP1
keys.description:
Time pulse length when locked to GNSS time (TP1) in [us]
Only used if CFG-TP-PULSE_LENGTH_DEF=LENGTH and CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1 is set.

keys.name: CFG-TP-DUTY_TP1
keys.description:
Time pulse duty cycle (TP1) in [%]
Only used if CFG-TP-PULSE_LENGTH_DEF=RATIO is set.

keys.name: CFG-TP-DUTY_LOCK_TP1
keys.description:
Time pulse duty cycle when locked to GNSS time (TP1) in [%]
Only used if CFG-TP-PULSE_LENGTH_DEF=RATIO and CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1 are set.

keys.name: CFG-TP-USER_DELAY_TP1
keys.description: User-configurable time pulse delay (TP1) in [ns]

keys.name: CFG-TP-TP1_ENA
keys.description:
Enable the time pulse (TP1)
if pin associated with time pulse is assigned for another function, the other function takes precedence.
Must be set for frequency-time products.

keys.name: CFG-TP-SYNC_GNSS_TP1
keys.description:
Sync time pulse to GNSS time or local clock (TP1)
If set, sync to GNSS if GNSS time is valid. Otherwise, use local clock.
This flag can be unset only in Timing product variants.

keys.name: CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1
keys.description:
Use locked parameters when possible (TP1)
If set, use CFG-TP-PERIOD_LOCK_TP1 and CFG-TP-LEN_LOCK_TP1 as soon as GNSS time is valid. Otherwise, use CFG-
TP-PERIOD_TP1 and CFG-TP-LEN_TP1.

keys.name: CFG-TP-ALIGN_TO_TOW_TP1
keys.description:
Align time pulse to top of second (TP1)
To use this feature, CFG-TP-SYNC_GNSS_TP1 must be set.

keys.name: CFG-TP-POL_TP1
keys.description:
Set time pulse polarity (TP1)
Time pulse period must be an integer fraction of 1 second.
false (0): falling edge at top of second.
true (1): rising edge at top of second.

keys.name: CFG-TP-TIMEGRID_TP1
keys.description:
Time grid to use (TP1)
Only relevant if CFG-TP-SYNC_GNSS_TP1 is set.
Note that configured GNSS time is estimated by the receiver if locked to any GNSS system. If the receiver has a valid
GNSS fix it attempts to steer the TP to the specified time grid even if the specified time is not based on information
from the constellation's satellites. To ensure timing based purely on a given GNSS, restrict the supported constellations
in CFG-SIGNAL-*.
See Table 48 below for a list of possible constants for this item.

keys.name: CFG-TP-DRSTR_TP1
keys.description:
Set drive strength of TP1
Time Pulse pin 1 (TP1) can support 4 possible drive strength cases: 2, 4, 8 and 12 mA
See Table 49 below for a list of possible constants for this item.

keys.description:
Enable the time pulse (TP1)
if pin associated with time pulse is assigned for another function, the other function takes precedence.
Must be set for frequency-time products.

keys.name: CFG-TP-SYNC_GNSS_TP1
keys.description:
Sync time pulse to GNSS time or local clock (TP1)
If set, sync to GNSS if GNSS time is valid. Otherwise, use local clock.
This flag can be unset only in Timing product variants.

keys.name: CFG-TP-USE_LOCKED_TP1
keys.description:
Use locked parameters when possible (TP1)
If set, use CFG-TP-PERIOD_LOCK_TP1 and CFG-TP-LEN_LOCK_TP1 as soon as GNSS time is valid. Otherwise, use CFG-
TP-PERIOD_TP1 and CFG-TP-LEN_TP1.

keys.name: CFG-TP-ALIGN_TO_TOW_TP1
keys.description:
Align time pulse to top of second (TP1)
To use this feature, CFG-TP-SYNC_GNSS_TP1 must be set.

keys.name: CFG-TP-POL_TP1
keys.description:
Set time pulse polarity (TP1)
Time pulse period must be an integer fraction of 1 second.
false (0): falling edge at top of second.
true (1): rising edge at top of second.

keys.name: CFG-TP-TIMEGRID_TP1
keys.description:
Time grid to use (TP1)
Only relevant if CFG-TP-SYNC_GNSS_TP1 is set.
Note that configured GNSS time is estimated by the receiver if locked to any GNSS system. If the receiver has a valid
GNSS fix it attempts to steer the TP to the specified time grid even if the specified time is not based on information
from the constellation's satellites. To ensure timing based purely on a given GNSS, restrict the supported constellations
in CFG-SIGNAL-*.
See Table 48 below for a list of possible constants for this item.

keys.name: CFG-TP-DRSTR_TP1
keys.description:
Set drive strength of TP1
Time Pulse pin 1 (TP1) can support 4 possible drive strength cases: 2, 4, 8 and 12 mA
See Table 49 below for a list of possible constants for this item.
